---
By: William G. Jordan
Locus:
  Page: 423
  Verse: 5
Tags:
  - Service
---
Self-confidence without self-reliance is as useless as a cooking recipe
without food. Self-confidence sees the possibilities of the individual;
self-reliance realizes them. Self-confidence sees the angel in the unhewn
block of marble; self-reliance carves it out for himself.
